Class SifImageFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.samsung.android.sdk.imagefilter.SifImageFilter

  • public class SifImageFilter
extends Object
    This class provides the image filter definitions and support for applying the filters.

    • Method Detail

      • filterImage

        public static void filterImage(Bitmap inputBitmap,
               int imageFilterOption,
               int filterLevel)
        Apply the specified image filter and filter level to the specified bitmap image.
        Use a mutable bitmap for InputBitmap since the bitmap is changed with this method.
        Parameters:
        inputBitmap - The mutable bitmap image that you want to change.
        imageFilterOption - The image filter that you want to apply to the image.
        The valid values for imageFilterOption are defined in the SifImageFilter class.
        If you set this parameter to FILTER_ORIGINAL, this method does not change the input bitmap.
        filterLevel - The filter level that you want to apply to the image.
        The valid values for filterLevel are defined in the SifImageFilter class. The valid values are:
        LEVEL_VERY_SMALL, LEVEL_SMALL, LEVEL_MEDIUM, LEVEL_LARGE, LEVEL_VERY_LARGE

      • filterImageCopy

        public static Bitmap filterImageCopy(Bitmap inputBitmap,
                     int imageFilterOption,
                     int filterLevel)
        Create a copy of the specified bitmap image and apply the specified image filter and filter level to it.
        Parameters:
        inputBitmap - The bitmap image that you want to copy and filter.
        imageFilterOption - The image filter that you want to apply to the image.
        The valid values for imageFilterOption are defined in the SifImageFilter class.
        If you set this parameter to FILTER_ORIGINAL, it returns a duplicate of the input bitmap.
        filterLevel - The filter level that you want to apply to the image.
        The valid values for filterLevel are defined in the SifImageFilter class. The valid values are: LEVEL_VERY_SMALL, LEVEL_SMALL, LEVEL_MEDIUM, LEVEL_LARGE, LEVEL_VERY_LARGE
        Returns:
        The duplicated bitmap after the specified image filter and filter level have been applied to it.

      • setImageTransparency

        public static void setImageTransparency(Bitmap inputBitmap,
                        int alpha)
        Set the transparency level for the specified bitmap image with the specified alpha value.
        Parameters:
        inputBitmap - The mutable bitmap image that you want to set a transparency level for.
        alpha The alpha value for the transparency level that you want to set.
        The valid range for alpha values is 0 to 255.
        alpha - The alpha value for the transparency level that you want to set.
        The valid range for alpha values is 0 to 255.
